com.microsoft.bingads.bulk.entities

Class BulkCampaignNegativeLocationTarget

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.microsoft.bingads.internal.bulk.BulkObject
      • com.microsoft.bingads.bulk.entities.BulkEntity
        • com.microsoft.bingads.internal.bulk.entities.MultiRecordBulkEntity
          • com.microsoft.bingads.bulk.entities.BulkCampaignNegativeLocationTarget

  • public class BulkCampaignNegativeLocationTarget
extends MultiRecordBulkEntity
    Represents a negative location target that is associated with a campaign. This class exposes the BulkLocationTargetWithStringLocation.getCityTarget(), BulkLocationTargetWithStringLocation.setCityTarget(com.microsoft.bingads.campaignmanagement.CityTarget) BulkLocationTargetWithStringLocation.getCountryTarget(), BulkLocationTargetWithStringLocation.setCountryTarget(com.microsoft.bingads.campaignmanagement.CountryTarget), BulkLocationTargetWithStringLocation.getMetroAreaTarget(), BulkLocationTargetWithStringLocation.setMetroAreaTarget(com.microsoft.bingads.campaignmanagement.MetroAreaTarget), BulkLocationTargetWithStringLocation.getPostalCodeTarget(), BulkLocationTargetWithStringLocation.setPostalCodeTarget(com.microsoft.bingads.campaignmanagement.PostalCodeTarget), BulkLocationTargetWithStringLocation.getStateTarget(), and BulkLocationTargetWithStringLocation.setStateTarget(com.microsoft.bingads.campaignmanagement.StateTarget) methods, that represent geographical location sub types. Each sub type can be read and written as fields of the Campaign Negative Location Target record in a bulk file.

    Each negative location sub type contains a list of bids. For example BulkLocationTargetWithStringLocation.getCityTarget() contains a list of CityTargetBid. Each CityTargetBid instance corresponds to one Campaign Location Target record in the bulk file. If you upload a BulkLocationTargetWithStringLocation.getCityTarget(), then you are effectively replacing any existing city bids for the corresponding negative location target.

    The BulkLocationTargetBidWithStringLocation.getLocationType() methods determines the geographical location sub type.

    For more information, see Campaign Negative Location Target at http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=511526.

    See Also:
    BulkServiceManager, BulkOperation, BulkFileReader, BulkFileWriter
